George M. KELLER, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. AMERICAN SALES BOOK COMPANY, Inc., Defendant-Appellee. (Two Actions Consolidated). No. 381. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. July 8, 1940. Plarry C. Kayser, of New York City (Earl D. Rader, of New York City, on the brief), for appellant. Stephen H. Philbin and William J. Barnes, both of New York City, for appellee.

Before SWAN, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and PATTERSON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed on the opinion below, D.C., 26 F.Supp. 835.
